gomodel:SYNGO_4512  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3a-g: SDS-digested replica immunogold labelling demonstrates that the Cav2.2 subunit of the voltage-gated Ca2+ channels is localized to the presynaptic active zone of CCK expressing GABAergic interneurons of the hippocampus.\nFigure 3i: The Cav2.2 subunit immunolabelling was abolished in Cav2.2-/- mice demonstrating the specificity of the antibody.\nS3c-d: Co-labelling of axon terminal with CB1 (10 nm gold) and Cav2.2 subunit (15 nm gold) further shows localisation of Cav2.2 immunogold particles in the active zone (inset: putative AZs are coloured in orange).\n\n12/01/2021 Dnyanada: The paper uses active zone marker RIM1/2 labelling to mark the active zone. They justify not using colocalisation experiments as the primary antibodies used for both Cav2.2 and the active zone marker RIM1/2 are raised in the same species (rabbits).\nThe annotation is linked to the Uniprot accession ID for mouse, however, it should be noted that both rat and mouse were used for the EM data.. Experimental description: Male Wistar rats (P30-P46, 40.8±6.6, n=5), CCK-BAC/DsRedT3 mice (P19-P25, 22.9±2.5, n=2 female, n=7 male), CB1+/+ (P18, P26, n=2 female) CB1-/- (P18, n=2 female), Cav2.2+/+ (P18, n=1) and Cav2.2-/- (9 months old, n=1) mice were used for the SDS-digested freeze-fracture replica-labelling EM experiments." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-05-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4512" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

